d to- he and his wife were also overly dressed). The owner apologized to him (the man and his wife waited awhile to be seated), but to no avail. Anyway, the man was seated at our table, and he didn't like being so close to John's daughters (he may have noticed that they were sick, but I think this really had to do with them being playful- still, they were pretty quiet and didn't make contact with anyone). The final straw came when John was helping a guy bus our area. A napkin fell on the man (it landed by his hands), and he could barely restrain himself (the napkin, by the way, hadn't been used). Anyway, John and I knew that it was "time to go" (I'm sorry, but I hope his food gave the man the runs). The layout is poor, but Smoque lives up to its name. The meat is cooked "Low And Slow," and is very smokey. If you have to wait, your food will be worth it for the most part. Still, I don't see what all the fuss is about.
